<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5369678>
    dc:description "Figure 37. Hypselospinus cf. fittoni. NHMUK R1831. Teeth. A, dentary tooth in lingual view (isolated specimen on stub of matrix); B, maxillary tooth in labial view. C−E, dentary replacement crowns embedded in the alveolar bone of the dentary. Abbreviations: m, mammillae on the marginal denticles; p, primary ridge; r, minor ridges; st, strand-like ridges." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5369678/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

